news.title: Guangzhou, Shenzhen told to allocate 10% of land for affordable rental homes
news.para: Under proposed new rules, rental housing will focus on the development of homes no larger than 70 square metres in area for new residents and young people.

news.title: House prices in UK jump 0.9% in October: Halifax
news.para: It brought the average house price to 270,027 pounds ($364,374)- up 8.1% on October 2020 and marking the strongest annual growth rate for four months.

news.title: Chinese banks quicken home loan disbursement but caution prevails
news.para: Authorities do not want genuine buyers to be shut out of the market or developers to face delays in receiving payments due to slow loan disbursements in a market whose health is key to the economy.

news.title: Residential buildings with EV charging stations may see price rise of 2-5%: JLL
news.para: Depending on type of buildings, these retrofit projects will have a major impact on pricing of residential asset class and will also help in efficient utilisation of real estate.

news.title: Demand for houses in Mysuru spikes as on-campus classes resume
news.para: For instance, in Bogadi, RR Nagar, Dattagalli and Vijayanagar areas in Mysuru city, rent for a two-bedroom house, which was between Rs 8,000 to Rs 10,000, has now increased to anywhere between Rs 11,000 and Rs 12,000.

news.title: Rising rents taking up growing share of Americans' income
news.para: Households with a median U.S. rent of $1,179 in August tapped 30.3% of their monthly income to pay their rent, up from 29.4% a year earlier, according to an analysis by Zillow.

news.title: Tiny house in wealthy Boston suburb sells for $315,000
news.para: The roughly 250-square-foot (23-square-meter) home in Newton sold on Monday for $315,000, according to Coldwell Banker Realty's Hans Brings Results agency.

news.title: Brookfield looks to buy majority stake in Alstria Office REIT AG for $4.1 billion
news.para: Brookfield announced a takeover offer of almost 3.5 billion euros ($4.1 billion) for Alstria on Thursday. It is aiming for a majority stake of more than 50%.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group halts trading as property woes grow
news.para: For now, all eyes are on a key Saturday deadline for Evergrande to pay an $82.5 million coupon on a bond. The firm missed the initial payment last month but was given a 30-day grace period. It has stumped up for two others in recent weeks.

news.title: Omaxe lease out 10.5 lakh sq ft space between Apr-Oct 2021
news.para: In Greater Noida, the company has leased 6.77 lakh sq ft, 2.95 lakh sq ft in Lucknow, 58,222 sq ft in Faridabad, and 20,000 sq ft in Amritsar.

news.title: Chinese developers' shares, bonds stumble again
news.para: In early trade in Hong Kong, a sub-index tracking the mainland property sector fell more than 2%, deepening its losses in the past two weeks to nearly 20%. An index of real estate A-shares fell more than 1.6% against a 0.25% drop in the broader blue-chip index.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group's unit misses payment, debt worries mount
news.para: Kaisa's troubles come amid concerns about a deepening liquidity crisis in the Chinese property sector, with a string of offshore debt defaults, credit rating downgrades, and sell offs in the developers' shares and bonds in recent weeks.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board got Rs 16 crore via online transactions in 22 months
news.para: Besides, the board had received over Rs one crore through online transactions in the months of February Rs 1.32 crore; March Rs 1.32 crore; May Rs 1.51 crore; July Rs 1.02 crore and August Rs 1.94 crore.

news.title: Gujarat: Ceramic tile prices up 10% after gas price revision
news.para: "Tile prices have been increased by 10% with effect from November 1. The prices have been revised thrice in the past three months due to the increased prices of natural gas and other fuels," said Mukesh Kundariya, president, vitrified tiles division, MCA.

news.title: Mumbai: 19 tenants of Gajanan Colony get redeveloped flats after seven years
news.para: The court had heard a petition by 19 out of 120 tenants of the Gajanan Colony, which comprised four buildings, at Eksar Pahadi. They had vacated their homes in 2014, and though the redeveloped building was ready & OC had been granted in February 2021, Earth Graphics did not hand over possession.
